class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2532906\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 02, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104uyk1665702991853.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/uyk1665702991853.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/uyk1665702991853.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"uyk1665702991853\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Configuring the Web Environment on Windows\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Uniface provides a complete web deployment environment for testing and deploying web applications and web services. The default installation includes a fully-configured Apache Tomcat HTTP Server and servlet engine. However, after installation, you can configure another web server and servlet engine to work with Uniface.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"uyk1665702991853__context_w1710ab1b5b1_w1711ab1b5_w1712ab1\">\n<div class=\"div prereq\" id=\"uyk1665702991853__topic_d65597e1_d65598e1_d65599e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"uyk1665702991853__p_d65600e1_d65601e1_d65602e1\">To configure your own web environment for Uniface, you need:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"uyk1665702991853__li_d28523e1_d28524e1_d28525e1\">J2EE-compliant web server, which can run Java servlets as J2EE web containers.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"uyk1665702991853__li_d28526e1_d28527e1_d28528e1\">Uniface Web Application Server (WASV), consisting of the Uniface Server, the Uniface Router, and the Uniface Web Request Dispatcher (WRD).\n </li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"div context\" id=\"uyk1665702991853__topic_d65603e1_d65604e1_d65605e1\">\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"uyk1665702991853__note_w1713ab1b5b1b3b1_w1714ab1b5b1b3_w1715ab1b5b1_w1716ab1b5_w1717ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> The following procedure is not required for the default web test environment.</div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"uyk1665702991853__p_d65606e1_d65607e1_d65608e1\">To configure the web environment:</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step\" id=\"uyk1665702991853__li_d28529e1_d28530e1_d28531e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Configure the web server and servlet engine to run Uniface servlets. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mmb1665702745202.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mmb1665702745202.html\" title=\"Uniface automatically installs the Apache Tomcat Web Server, which is used for developing testing Uniface web applications and web services. In a production environment, you can use Tomcat as the web server for your deployed application, but you can use any Jakarta EE (Enterprise Edition) compliant web server with support for the Servlet 6.0 specification or higher.\">Configure a Web Server for Uniface Applications</a>.\n                  </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"uyk1665702991853__li_d28532e1_d28533e1_d28534e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Configure the Uniface Web Application Server. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qsb1665702750396.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qsb1665702750396.html\" title=\"The Uniface Web Application Server (WASV) is automatically configured to work with the default Apache Tomcat web server, so you only need to perform this task if you are creating your own web deployment environment, or customizing the existing configuration.\">Configuring the Uniface Web Application Server</a>.\n                  </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"uyk1665702991853__li_d28535e1_d28536e1_d28537e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">If you want to run the Tomcat servlet engine under Microsoft IIS, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ceb1665702762718.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ceb1665702762718.html\" title=\"You can use a Microsoft Internet Information Services (IIS) web server to deploy Uniface web applications. However, because IIS cannot execute servlets such as the Uniface WRD and SRD, it must redirect client requests to the Tomcat servlet engine. To do so it uses the Apache ISAPI Redirector, also known as the IIS connector.\">Configuring Microsoft IIS to Use Tomcat</a>.\n </span>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bhq1665702755013.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Deploying Uniface Web Applications</a><p>The Uniface default installation includes a fully-configured Apache Tomcat HTTP Server and servlet engine for testing and deploying Uniface web applications. For production deployment, you can configure another web server and servlet engine to run Uniface applications after installation.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tza1665702752637.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Deploying a Uniface Web Service</a></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532906\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532906\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Configuring the Web Environment on Windows Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 02, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Configuring the Web Environment on Windows Uniface provides a complete web deployment environment for testing and deploying web applications and web services. The default installation includes a fully-configured Apache Tomcat HTTP Server and servlet engine. However, after installation, you can configure another web server and servlet engine to work with Uniface. To configure your own web environment for Uniface, you need: J2EE-compliant web server, which can run Java servlets as J2EE web containers. Uniface Web Application Server (WASV), consisting of the Uniface Server, the Uniface Router, and the Uniface Web Request Dispatcher (WRD). Note: The following procedure is not required for the default web test environment. To configure the web environment: Configure the web server and servlet engine to run Uniface servlets. For more information, see Configure a Web Server for Uniface Applications . Configure the Uniface Web Application Server. For more information, see Configuring the Uniface Web Application Server . If you want to run the Tomcat servlet engine under Microsoft IIS, see Configuring Microsoft IIS to Use Tomcat . Related Links Deploying Uniface Web Applications The Uniface default installation includes a fully-configured Apache Tomcat HTTP Server and servlet engine for testing and deploying Uniface web applications. For production deployment, you can configure another web server and servlet engine to run Uniface applications after installation. Deploying a Uniface Web Service Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}